UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1972
1 Major Richard Star Act, highlighting its importance in ensuring a veteran with a
2 disability receives the benefits he or she rightfully earned; and
3 WHEREAS, Congress has a duty to care for veterans with disabilities by ensuring
4 they receive the support and benefits earned through their service; and
5 WHEREAS, veterans with disabilities have advocated for the elimination of this
6 offset, underscoring the physical, psychological, and financial burdens they face due to
7 the current policy; and
8 WHEREAS, the Major Richard Star Act aligns with the nation's commitment to
9 honor and support all veterans, including those in Kentucky, by ensuring they receive the
10 full benefits they earned through their service, regardless of their length of service; and
11 WHEREAS, the General Assembly recognizes the urgent need to address this
12 injustice and support veterans with disabilities who have sacrificed for our nation;
13 NOW, THEREFORE,
14 Be it resolved by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
15 Section 1. The General Assembly of Kentucky hereby urges the United States
16 Congress to pass the Major Richard Star Act (H.R. 2102, S. 1032) to ensure veterans with
17 disabilities receive their full United States Department of Defense retirement pay and
18 United States Department of Veterans Affairs disability compensation without offset.
19 Section 2. The Clerk of the Senate is directed to transmit a copy of this
20 Resolution to the President and Vice President of the United States, the Speaker of the
21 United States House of Representatives, the Majority Leader of the United States Senate,
22 members of the Kentucky congressional delegation, and to sponsor and co-sponsors of
23 this Resolution for distribution.
